boolean isGeometric = true;
for(int i=1; i<sequence.length; i++){
 if(sequence[i] - sequence[i-1] != sequence[1] - sequence[0]){
 isArithmetic = false;
 }
 if(sequence[i] / sequence[i-1] != sequence[1] / sequence[0]){
 isGeometric = false;
 }
}
// print result
if(isArithmetic){
 System.out.println("The sequence is arithmetic with common difference: " + (sequence[1] - sequence[0]));
}
else if(isGeometric){
 System.out.println("The sequence is geometric with common ratio: " + (sequence[1] / sequence[0]));
}
else{
 System.out.println("The sequence is neither arithmetic nor geometric");

### Response:
This Java code will determine if the given sequence of numbers is arithmetic or geometric and calculate the common difference or ratio accordingly. In this case, the sequence provided is {1, 5, 9, 13, 17}. The code first initializes the sequence array and then checks if the sequence is arithmetic or geometric using a for loop. 
If the sequence is arithmetic, the code sets the isArithmetic boolean to true and calculates the common difference by subtracting the second element from the first element. If the sequence is geometric, the code sets the isGeometric boolean to true and calculates the common ratio by dividing the second element by the first element. 
Finally, the code prints the result by checking whether the sequence is arithmetic or geometric or neither. If the sequence is arithmetic, it prints the common difference. If the sequence is geometric, it prints the common ratio. If the sequence is neither arithmetic nor geometric, it prints a message indicating that the sequence is not arithmetic or geometric.

